          "scid": "thig2.10:1.0.3",
          "en": "10. Sāmā"
        },
        {
          "scid": "thig2.10:1.0.4",
          "en": "“Four times, nay, five, I sallied from my cell, And roamed afield to find the peace of mind I sought in vain, and governance of thoughts I could not bring into captivity."
        },
        {
          "scid": "thig2.10:1.0.5",
          "en": "To me, even to me, on that eighth day It came: all craving ousted from my heart. ‘Mid many sore afflictions, I had wrought With passionate endeavour, and had won! Craving was dead, and the Lord’s will was done.”"
        }
      ],
